abstract: The Commodity Futures Trading Commission filed a record number of enforcement cases over the last year as it moved to clean up the mess from the financial crisis.

lead_paragraph: The Commodity Futures Trading Commission, once a sleepy Wall Street watchdog, is exercising its regulatory muscle, filing a record number of enforcement cases over the last year as it moved to clean up the mess from the financial crisis.

headline.main: Wall Street Watchdog Finds Its Teeth
